title: License fee
context: §605-5 License fee. The clerk of the supreme court shall exact from every practitioner, upon the practitioner&rsquo;s receiving a license, an admission fee of $10, for the benefit of the State. [CC 1859, §1073; RL 1925, §2308; RL 1935, §3607; RL 1945, §9705; RL 1955, §217-5; HRS §605-5; gen ch 1985]
